# Testing

## Simulator Destination

The project targets iOS. Use this destination for xcodebuild:

```
platform=iOS Simulator,name=iPhone 17 Pro Max,OS=26.2
```

## Running Tests

Run all tests:
```bash
xcodebuild test -scheme md2jpeg -destination 'platform=iOS Simulator,name=iPhone 17 Pro Max,OS=26.2'
```

Run a specific test class:
```bash
xcodebuild test -scheme md2jpeg -destination 'platform=iOS Simulator,name=iPhone 17 Pro Max,OS=26.2' -only-testing:md2jpegTests/MarkdownHTMLRendererTests
```

## Known Issues

- `PreviewDrawerBehaviorTests.swift` has a pre-existing compilation error (`PreviewDrawerBehavior` type not found). Temporarily rename it to `.swift.disabled` if it blocks the test target from compiling.
- Two Mermaid CSS polish tests (`testRendererIncludesMermaidContainerAndSVGPolishInClassicTheme`, `testRendererSupportsMultipleMermaidDiagramTypesFixture`) have stale CSS assertions and fail pre-existing.
